translated: Öster, Anders Emanuel, former mayor, Söderköping, born on October 19, 1888 in N. Finnskoga, Värmland County, son of landowner Jan Ö. and Sara Jonsson. Married on the 23rd with Karin Rosén. — Completed studies in Karlstad in 1906, law degree in Uppsala in 1917. Became mayor of Söderköping in 1923. Chairman of the board for the savings bank, the Östergötland Private Bank in Söderköping, and the school board for the secondary school in Söderköping. Vice chairman of the board for the Norrköping-Söderköping-Vikbolandet Railway Co. since 1937. Received the Royal Order of Vasa in 1941.
